originalText.text:
The reviews here are accurate. They shrunk and ruined a $200 cashmere sweater (it would maybe fit a pumpkin now) and wouldn’t do anything about it. I also dropped off a jacket to have the zipper fixed, they quoted me $50, I asked for it back, and it’s been over a month with no update.

If you live in The Eugene, don’t fall for the convenience. Go elsewhere

originalText.text:
What a joke of a place. Our building uses this palce as it's cleaners. long story short we have sent things here for 3 years and today was the final day. We sent a $400 sweater that when recieved back was torn in the front. We called and explained what happened. We asked to send pictures instead of send it in so we could be reimbursed. They told us "We only reimbuse up to 10 times the amount of the receipt." or give "Store credit". No, we're not using store credit or your store ever again.

What this also means is if they mess up your $500 or $1,000 suit you can get bent if your total cost is $20 for a simple cleaning.

This is one of many inccidents we've had. We've had a sweater shrunk, anouther sweater recolored??, clothes that smell TERRIBLE coming back and now this. If you want to lose money, this is the perfect place for you.

Unreal.

originalText.text: They charged my card ~$25 when the receipt total was only $22. Whats also annoying it that they billed me for 18 pounds of laundry when my laundry bag only weighs 14 lbs. I appreciate them washing and folding my clothes and pairing my socks. It saves me time. But overall, it is not worth it. The clothes don't come back smelling clean, my dress shirts need ironing before I can where them to work, and I can tell that my clothes are wearing out faster. Moral of Story: get a place with a washer and dryer.

originalText.text: I think a goat and typewriter could give better customer service. At least the goat is funny. We booked a cleaning appointment a week in advance and they no showed. When we called to ask the status, she said she didn’t know and would call back. Hilariously inept. Frustrating since I live in the building and it’d be convenient.

originalText.text: They are quick and friendly, but take no pride in their work. I have had shirts come back that shrunk, stains that have not been removed, and they don't replace buttons like other cleaners. Really it's just an expensive way to iron your dress shirts...
